OL,3,C'Set up was a nightmare': Firms under
OL,4,Cpressure as pension deadline looms
OL,6,FThe President of Employment and Social
OL,7,FSecurity, Deputy Tina Bury, says: "We
OL,8,Flooked at comparable jurisdictions,
OL,9,Fespecially where it is mandatory, and
OL,10,Fit was felt that bringing in a
OL,11,Fsecondary pension as mandatory was a
OL,12,Fbit of a step too far at this stage.
OL,14,F"It is important and will perhaps be
OL,15,Fconsidered in the future, how we
OL,16,Fsupport those people (on a minimum
OL,17,Fwage) to make sure that they can save."
OL,19,FThe impetus is now on the employer to
OL,20,Ffully understand the rules.
